<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 8: TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER -
        FRONT COVER, REAR HALF
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FRONT COVER, REAR HALF</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gears removed, remove rear half of front cover as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the nine retaining bolts which secure the front cover to the crankcase. Refer
                        to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e160_223.xml" xrefid="ef1600821">8.21</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lift the front cover (with dowels) off the crankcase.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Discard the O-Ring and clean any sealing material from the front cover or
                        crankcase.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
